<Action id="28855" issue="18616" author="andrey.goncharov" type="comment" created="2017-07-23 11:58:57.0" updateauthor="andrey.goncharov" updated="2017-07-23 11:58:57.0"> <body><! CDATA  ~krw910  please take a look at the demo I recorded on the very machine you have troubles with.   https://drive.google.com/open?id=0BxskuV-A2bahYkJNUmZXQnFzWEU   As to your installation on AWS, it looks like you run apt-get install directly from root. This way our scripts do not know where transaction files should be copied. If you connect to client1 machine you'll see there's .sovrin folder in /home. It most probably happens because you run install from root. I'd advise you to run install from the user you want to work as with elevated (sudo) privileges  P.S. I also slacked it to you in case you can't play it  ></body> </Action>
<Action id="28866" issue="18616" author="krw910" type="comment" body="Turns out our install scripts are installing as root and this is a know issue with installing as root. If you install as the user it works." created="2017-07-23 19:19:56.0" updateauthor="krw910" updated="2017-07-23 19:19:56.0"/>
